The paper proposes a new gating mechanism for recurrent neural networks and evaluates its effectiveness on synthetic tasks, language modeling tasks, and scene text recognition benchmarks. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) for its focus on neural networks, cs.CL (Computation and Language) for its evaluation on language modeling tasks, cs.LG (Machine Learning) for its focus on improving learning performance, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) for its evaluation on scene text recognition benchmarks, and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) for its overall focus on improving the performance of recurrent neural networks.
